    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Method for analyzing the image of a textured object into a set of quantitative measurements revealing its qualities described by terms such as rough, smooth, silky, or bumpy as a function of the spatial variation in pixel intensities. The sample images can be obtained through various digital image processing methods, including diffraction-based analyses.</Note_Text>
